  "course_description": "Descriptions of, explanations for, and treatment of the major adult psychological disorders.",
  "course_notes": "(Prior completion of Psyc 110, or Psyc 111, or AP/IB credit in psychology) (Coverage of all major adult psychological disorders in terms of their etiology, diagnosis, and treatment. Particular emphasis will be placed on: (1) exposing students to the major theoretical and conceptual models of abnormal behavior, and (2) providing students with the skills to become more critical consumers of the burgeoning literature on psychopathology.)",
